step 1 :-
project initialization 

npm install express typeorm reflect-metadata mysql2 bcrypt jsonwebtoken cookie-parser express-validator express-rate-limit helmet cors dotenv multer
npm install --save-dev typescript ts-node nodemon @types/express @types/bcrypt @types/jsonwebtoken @types/cookie-parser @types/cors @types/multer @types/node

this will create tsconfig.json file in the root directory of your project which will contain the configuration for the TypeScript compiler. You can customize this file according to your project's needs.
-> npx tsc --init


Step 2 — 
Database Schema Design & TypeORM Entity Modeling
Design all entities:

Frontend sends requestAngular service triggers a POST request to /orders with productId and quantity.
02
Route matches endpointExpress route definition catches the request and attaches middleware and controller.
03
Middleware processes requestAuthentication, validation, and logging middleware run before business logic.
04
Controller delegates to serviceController receives request and calls OrderService to handle purchase logic.
05
Service executes business rulesService checks stock, calculates total, creates order and order items.
06
Repository saves to databaseTypeORM repositories persist order, order items, and update product stock.
07
Response returned to frontendController sends JSON response with order confirmation back to Angular UI.